            "doi": "10.1093/bioinformatics/btz480",
            "metadata": {
                "abstract": "\u00a9 The Author(s) 2019. Published by Oxford University Press. All rights reserved.Capture-C is a member of the chromosome-conformation-capture family of experimental methods which probes the 3D organization of chromosomes within the cell nucleus. It provides high-resolution information on the genome-wide chromatin interactions from a set of 'target' genomic locations, and is growing in popularity as a tool for improving our understanding of cisregulation and gene function. Yet, analysis of the data is complicated, and to date there has been no dedicated or easy-to-use software to automate the process. We present capC-MAP, a software package for the analysis of Capture-C data.",
